s between their observed continuum shapes are\ndue to higher nuclear reddening in radio-selected AGNs, and additional\nreddening from dust further out in the host galaxies in radio-quiet AGNs. Our\nconclusions have important implications for the modelling of quasar continua\nand the analysis of quasar demographics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Sep 2003 19:25:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Mar 2004 23:07:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 14 Jul 2004 23:01:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
