o measure, being related to the third and fourth terms in the\nTaylor series expansion of the Hubble law, it becomes clear why direct\nobservational constraints on the cosmological equation of state are so\nrelatively weak; and are likely to remain weak for the foreseeable future.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Sep 2003 04:08:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Sep 2003 22:25:25 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 5 Dec 2003 02:35:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 31 Mar 2004 02:48:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
